<div style="text-align: left;" align="left">
<p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="center"><span style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;"><b> Meet Kalyn!&nbsp;</b></span></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS,Geneva; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="left"><span style="font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">This issue's featured sitter is Kalyn Polatty, who has been with Rocket City Sitters since December 2009.<span>&nbsp; </span>Kalyn first learned about RCS while taking a CPR class with other sitters.</img></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="left"><span style="font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="left"><span style="font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">One of the main reasons Kalyn became a sitter with RCS is because she really likes working with children and this company gives her an opportunity to do so.<span>&nbsp; </span>Through RCS, she is regular afterschool sitter for a family in Madison, helping with snacks and overseeing homework. She is also frequently requested by other local families who want a fun and dependable sitter during their date nights and other weekend activities.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="left"><span style="font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">&nbsp;</span></p>

<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="left"><span style="font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">Kalyn graduated from the University of Alabama where she studied infant, childhood and adolescent development, earning a Bachelor of Science in Human Development.<span>&nbsp; </span>In addition, she has experience as a preschool teacher and has babysat extensively for families with children of all ages. Currently, Kalyn is also the Nursery Coordinator at Grace United Methodist Church, teaches Zumba and, when the weather is warm, enjoys hiking at Monte Sano Mountain. </span></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="left"><span style="font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" align="left"><span style="font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">Time and again families are impressed with her. Sonia F., mother of two, tell us, "Kalyn is wonderful! She is punctual, respectful to my family and our home, very engaged with my two small children. She even had my children's toys picked up, and was alert when my husband and I got home at 10:30 pm. My oldest keeps asking when 'Her friend will be coming over to play again.' That was enough for me; I knew we had found someone great!"&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>
